### Example 3: Message received by Recipient

Letâ€™s say that the Recipient is example.com  
Processing at example.com:

-       example.com performs usual authentication checks
-       example.com adds Authentication-Results: header, Received header
-       Determines that message fails DMARC
-       Checks for ARC-Seal: header; finds three
-       Validates the signature in the highest numbered (â€œi=2â€) ARC-Seal: header, which covers all previous ARC-Seal: and ARC-Authentication-Results: headers
-       Validates the other ARC-Seal header (â€œi=2â€), which covers the ARC-Authentication-Results: header
-       Validates the other ARC-Seal header (â€œi=1â€), which covers the d1.example ARC-Message-Signature: header
-       example.com uses the ARC-Authentication-Results: values

Hereâ€™s what the message looks like at this point:

~~~~~~~~~~
